1
00:00:35,076 --> 00:00:36,828
Hey!

2
00:00:36,911 --> 00:00:38,872
Matsu, not there. Over here.

3
00:00:38,955 --> 00:00:40,540
-Huh?
-Over here.

4
00:00:40,623 --> 00:00:43,376
-Not that way. This way.
-Ah.

5
00:00:48,089 --> 00:00:50,842
-Are you okay, Matsu?
-I'm not okay at all.

6
00:00:56,139 --> 00:00:58,266
You're really starting to look the part.

7
00:00:58,349 --> 00:00:59,517
You think so?

8
00:01:02,562 --> 00:01:06,649
I was surprised when I heard
you were coming back during the pandemic.

9
00:01:06,733 --> 00:01:10,945
But they do say caregiving
is physically demanding work too.

10
00:01:11,446 --> 00:01:14,824
I thought it'd be tough for you
to jump into manual labor,

11
00:01:14,908 --> 00:01:16,367
but you're keeping up well.

12
00:01:16,868 --> 00:01:18,328
Thank you.

13
00:01:23,500 --> 00:01:25,043
The boss seems happy too.

14
00:01:26,961 --> 00:01:28,421
Hmm, you think so?

15
00:01:29,464 --> 00:01:32,592
He probably just thinks
his son came tumbling back home.

16
00:01:33,510 --> 00:01:35,095
He may say this and that,

17
00:01:35,595 --> 00:01:38,431
but deep down,
having your child take over your job

18
00:01:38,515 --> 00:01:41,434
would make any dad happy.

19
00:01:41,518 --> 00:01:43,186
You're being a good son.

20
00:01:44,687 --> 00:01:45,939
I hope so.

21
00:01:47,190 --> 00:01:49,901
Okay, here we are.

22
00:01:49,984 --> 00:01:52,987
-Thank you, Grandma.
-Of course.

23
00:01:53,822 --> 00:01:55,156
All righty.

24
00:01:56,074 --> 00:01:57,325
Phew.

25
00:02:00,620 --> 00:02:02,914
-I'm home.
-Welcome back, Kanau.

26
00:02:04,082 --> 00:02:06,042
-I'm home.
-Welcome back.

27
00:02:06,126 --> 00:02:08,253
Here's a cold drink.

28
00:02:08,336 --> 00:02:10,130
I'm home!

29
00:02:10,213 --> 00:02:13,925
-We could develop a series that includes--
-I'm home!

30
00:02:14,425 --> 00:02:16,052
Excuse me for a moment.

31
00:02:16,136 --> 00:02:18,972
Here, Kanau. Go wash your hands.

32
00:02:19,055 --> 00:02:21,599
You know you need to wash your hands.

33
00:02:22,892 --> 00:02:26,312
If you don't, you won't get to eat
Grandma's hamburger steak.

34
00:02:26,396 --> 00:02:28,189
-Hamburger steak?
-Yeah.

35
00:02:31,734 --> 00:02:32,944
All right.

36
00:02:41,661 --> 00:02:43,454
Let's get the air out.

37
00:02:43,538 --> 00:02:46,207
One, two, three, four.

38
00:02:46,291 --> 00:02:49,335
Then, we grill it. There.

39
00:02:49,836 --> 00:02:51,087
And there.

40
00:02:51,713 --> 00:02:55,383
Careful! The oil might splatter.

41
00:02:55,466 --> 00:02:57,135
I wanna see!

42
00:02:57,218 --> 00:03:00,180
-The oil's hot. You'll get burned.
-I wanna see!

43
00:03:00,263 --> 00:03:03,057
Come here, Kanau. It's dangerous.

44
00:03:03,141 --> 00:03:05,518
-Did you do your homework?
-I'm done.

45
00:03:06,144 --> 00:03:09,189
I'll grill you up some tasty ones, okay?

46
00:03:09,272 --> 00:03:12,275
How about we go over there
and play pretend ice hockey?

47
00:03:12,358 --> 00:03:16,863
Sure. I'll play if you'll be the ball.

48
00:03:16,946 --> 00:03:20,283
What? Did you just call me a ball?

49
00:03:20,366 --> 00:03:22,619
You silly girl!

50
00:03:24,078 --> 00:03:25,830
Won't it get cramped?

51
00:03:26,414 --> 00:03:28,499
It'll be better for Kanau

52
00:03:28,583 --> 00:03:31,419
to have her own room
when she's older, right?

53
00:03:31,502 --> 00:03:33,213
Hurry, Mommy.

54
00:03:33,296 --> 00:03:35,506
-Well, that's true.
-Okay.

55
00:03:35,590 --> 00:03:37,300
Just under seven meters.

56
00:03:37,383 --> 00:03:40,011
-The problem is the entrance.
-Yeah.

57
00:03:44,224 --> 00:03:45,475
Sorry, just a second.

58
00:03:47,352 --> 00:03:48,228
Hello?

59
00:03:48,311 --> 00:03:51,689
<i>Hey. How're you doing?</i>

60
00:03:51,773 --> 00:03:53,483
I'm hanging in there.

61
00:03:53,566 --> 00:03:55,610
I've got muscle pain every day.

62
00:03:56,319 --> 00:03:59,447
Come on, build those muscles.
You're still young.

63
00:04:01,074 --> 00:04:02,575
<i>I'll do my best.</i>

64
00:04:04,244 --> 00:04:05,745
<i>How are things over there?</i>

65
00:04:05,828 --> 00:04:07,622
<i>It's the same as always.</i>

66
00:04:07,705 --> 00:04:08,957
Hmm.

67
00:04:09,457 --> 00:04:11,417
Well, you love working on-site.

68
00:04:11,501 --> 00:04:12,627
<i>I guess.</i>

69
00:04:14,837 --> 00:04:17,715
So, um…

70
00:04:19,384 --> 00:04:21,344
Congrats on your marriage.

71
00:04:23,763 --> 00:04:26,474
<i>I told you.</i>
<i>It's still at the planning stage.</i>

72
00:04:28,101 --> 00:04:30,853
I've been with my partner six years,
and nothing's happened.

73
00:04:32,438 --> 00:04:35,817
Oh? I didn't know
you wanted to get married.

74
00:04:36,317 --> 00:04:39,654
<i>I do, just like everyone else.</i>
<i>Got a problem with that?</i>

75
00:04:40,989 --> 00:04:44,075
No, not at all.

76
00:04:47,203 --> 00:04:48,413
<i>When's the ceremony?</i>

77
00:04:49,998 --> 00:04:50,999
Oh, no.

78
00:04:51,916 --> 00:04:54,377
This is for Kanau's sake.

79
00:04:55,461 --> 00:04:56,629
We'll just register it.

80
00:04:59,007 --> 00:05:00,216
I see.

81
00:05:01,259 --> 00:05:03,219
I'll send you a gift.

82
00:05:03,303 --> 00:05:05,596
<i>No, you don't have to.</i>

83
00:05:05,680 --> 00:05:06,514
Why not?

84
00:05:06,597 --> 00:05:08,099
It's fine.

85
00:05:08,599 --> 00:05:10,059
<i>That's all I wanted to say.</i>

86
00:05:10,560 --> 00:05:12,353
Come visit us once in a while.

87
00:05:13,062 --> 00:05:16,816
We've been short-staffed
ever since you quit.

88
00:05:18,234 --> 00:05:19,527
-Okay.
-<i>Yeah.</i>

89
00:05:19,610 --> 00:05:21,696
-Thank you.
-<i>Sure.</i>

90
00:05:22,280 --> 00:05:24,907
"The sky turned rosy pink,

91
00:05:24,991 --> 00:05:29,996
and the sun quietly rose."

92
00:05:30,079 --> 00:05:30,997
Okay.

93
00:05:31,497 --> 00:05:33,124
The end.

94
00:05:33,207 --> 00:05:35,043
All right. Let's go to bed.

95
00:05:35,126 --> 00:05:38,504
But I'm not sleepy yet.

96
00:05:38,588 --> 00:05:41,799
You're going shopping
with Mommy and Granny tomorrow, right?

97
00:05:41,883 --> 00:05:43,384
Yeah, and you too.

98
00:05:43,885 --> 00:05:47,847
I've got plans with Gramps tomorrow,
so I can't go.

99
00:05:47,930 --> 00:05:49,390
What?

100
00:05:50,516 --> 00:05:53,061
Okay, say goodnight to Daddy.

101
00:05:53,144 --> 00:05:54,228
Good night.

102
00:05:54,312 --> 00:05:56,731
Good. Let's go to bed then.

103
00:06:02,445 --> 00:06:03,946
All right.

104
00:06:05,448 --> 00:06:07,450
Okay, close your eyes.

105
00:06:09,827 --> 00:06:11,913
I'll stay here until you fall asleep.

106
00:06:11,996 --> 00:06:13,414
-Okay.
-Yeah.

107
00:06:25,927 --> 00:06:27,762
-Is she asleep?
-Yeah.

108
00:06:27,845 --> 00:06:29,847
She's even snoring a little.

109
00:06:38,648 --> 00:06:40,441
Haven't you gotten busier

110
00:06:40,525 --> 00:06:42,944
since you went independent
and started working remotely?

111
00:06:43,027 --> 00:06:46,072
Hmm, that's true.

112
00:06:46,572 --> 00:06:50,868
A lot of people have been
moving back home or relocating.

113
00:06:50,952 --> 00:06:54,205
I feel like I'm able to do more
of what I want to now

114
00:06:54,288 --> 00:06:56,457
than when I lived in the city.

115
00:06:57,417 --> 00:06:58,418
Nice.

116
00:07:01,003 --> 00:07:04,340
It's because you work hard for it.

117
00:07:07,218 --> 00:07:08,094
You think so?

118
00:07:08,177 --> 00:07:10,138
Of course.

119
00:07:16,727 --> 00:07:17,687
These were good.

120
00:08:00,438 --> 00:08:03,191
Let's knock this down
and build Kanau's room here.

121
00:08:05,610 --> 00:08:08,029
Are you sure Uncle won't get mad?

122
00:08:09,113 --> 00:08:10,656
It's the other way around.

123
00:08:11,157 --> 00:08:15,703
He's probably thrilled up there
knowing you guys are going to live here.

124
00:08:17,663 --> 00:08:19,290
I hope so.

125
00:08:20,291 --> 00:08:23,586
And you know, the funny thing about houses

126
00:08:23,669 --> 00:08:26,589
is that they deteriorate
when no one lives in them.

127
00:08:27,089 --> 00:08:31,844
I guess they get lonely
when there's no one around.

128
00:08:43,022 --> 00:08:46,400
Now we just have to decide
what to do with these paintings.

129
00:08:46,484 --> 00:08:48,110
Yeah.

130
00:08:52,615 --> 00:08:53,950
Hmm.

131
00:09:10,091 --> 00:09:11,300
What's this?

132
00:09:38,202 --> 00:09:39,829
It's him.

133
00:09:43,499 --> 00:09:48,546
Did Johan ever come by
to see you guys on his own?

134
00:09:49,755 --> 00:09:50,756
No.

135
00:09:53,134 --> 00:09:54,343
What?

136
00:13:16,796 --> 00:13:18,088
I wonder…

137
00:13:20,216 --> 00:13:21,967
what was up with him.

138
00:14:01,173 --> 00:14:03,342
Those were fun times.

139
00:14:09,807 --> 00:14:12,226
When you came to Berlin…

140
00:14:15,312 --> 00:14:17,898
When I got to meet Seiichi…

141
00:14:19,024 --> 00:14:24,697
And when the four of us lived together.

142
00:14:59,523 --> 00:15:01,650
It was about a year ago.

143
00:15:04,278 --> 00:15:05,821
Sua…

144
00:15:08,490 --> 00:15:10,117
reached out to me.

145
00:15:19,501 --> 00:15:21,128
She said Johan…

146
00:15:26,508 --> 00:15:28,052
is sick.

147
00:15:34,099 --> 00:15:35,434
Right now…

148
00:15:38,187 --> 00:15:40,439
he's in a hospital in Germany.

149
00:15:53,494 --> 00:15:54,828
I see.

150
00:16:01,293 --> 00:16:03,003
Kanau and I…

151
00:16:05,130 --> 00:16:06,757
We'll be fine.

152
00:16:22,731 --> 00:16:24,566
-I'm giving you medicine.
-Okay.

153
00:16:31,615 --> 00:16:32,908
Are you ready?

154
00:16:32,992 --> 00:16:35,661
Just one second.

155
00:16:36,620 --> 00:16:40,833
I need to do this, and then this.

156
00:16:43,544 --> 00:16:44,753
I got it.

157
00:16:48,340 --> 00:16:49,883
So, are you ready?

158
00:16:50,968 --> 00:16:52,094
Yeah.

159
00:16:53,721 --> 00:16:55,347
I'll start recording.

160
00:16:56,432 --> 00:16:59,268
One, two, three.

161
00:17:15,034 --> 00:17:16,452
I…

162
00:17:19,038 --> 00:17:21,665
lived my life

163
00:17:23,417 --> 00:17:26,503
not wanting anything…

164
00:17:30,883 --> 00:17:34,511
and giving up on everything.

165
00:17:36,555 --> 00:17:38,557
<i>When I was 14 years old,</i>

166
00:17:40,142 --> 00:17:42,061
<i>our mother died.</i>

167
00:17:43,437 --> 00:17:47,316
<i>-Sua and I became orphans.</i>
-Welcome home.

168
00:17:48,776 --> 00:17:50,986
<i>Our relatives swarmed around</i>

169
00:17:51,695 --> 00:17:56,992
<i>for the little money our mother left us.</i>

170
00:17:58,619 --> 00:18:00,370
Sua, let's eat.

171
00:18:00,454 --> 00:18:04,291
<i>We couldn't trust the people</i>
<i>at the orphanage we were sent to either.</i>

172
00:18:06,001 --> 00:18:11,006
<i>So Sua and I decided to live on our own.</i>

173
00:18:11,090 --> 00:18:13,050
You should say thank you first.

174
00:18:13,967 --> 00:18:15,219
Thank you.

175
00:18:15,928 --> 00:18:19,848
<i>At the time, I was at rock bottom.</i>

176
00:18:23,143 --> 00:18:25,562
What are you doing?

177
00:18:26,688 --> 00:18:28,565
You're so clumsy.

178
00:18:28,649 --> 00:18:34,279
<i>While working, I began boxing at school.</i>

179
00:18:35,864 --> 00:18:38,909
<i>-This helped me distract myself.</i>
-Finish this up.

180
00:18:40,244 --> 00:18:41,286
Yes, sir.

181
00:18:41,370 --> 00:18:43,163
<i>Boxing was great.</i>

182
00:18:44,081 --> 00:18:49,920
<i>It's a simple world</i>
<i>where strength decides everything.</i>

183
00:18:52,673 --> 00:18:56,802
<i>This was around the time</i>
<i>I first discovered manga too.</i>

184
00:19:02,724 --> 00:19:06,478
<i>I liked stories.</i>

185
00:19:06,562 --> 00:19:07,896
PHOENIX
TEZUKA OSAMU COLLECTION

186
00:19:07,980 --> 00:19:10,190
<i>They were a world of my own.</i>

187
00:19:12,526 --> 00:19:14,111
<i>But reality…</i>

188
00:19:14,611 --> 00:19:17,739
Try hitting me.
You're just a little shrimp.

189
00:19:17,823 --> 00:19:19,199
<i>…was different.</i>

190
00:19:19,700 --> 00:19:23,829
It's his fault!
Why's he giving me all the work?

191
00:19:23,912 --> 00:19:25,873
No one ever complains to him!

192
00:19:25,956 --> 00:19:28,709
<i>I used to think everyone else was trash.</i>

193
00:19:30,377 --> 00:19:33,297
<i>And they were.</i>

194
00:19:37,092 --> 00:19:39,511
You all do so well
with your parents around.

195
00:19:43,640 --> 00:19:46,018
Sorry, excuse me.

196
00:19:46,101 --> 00:19:48,270
Who can solve this problem?

197
00:19:50,856 --> 00:19:51,899
Anyone?

198
00:19:52,941 --> 00:19:54,860
-Me.
-Miss Hwang Sua.

199
00:19:57,613 --> 00:20:00,324
-I'll answer from here.
-Go ahead.

200
00:20:01,491 --> 00:20:04,244
X is negative 7 over 11.

201
00:20:04,328 --> 00:20:08,665
You managed to calculate it in your head.
Everyone, let's give her a hand.

202
00:20:08,749 --> 00:20:10,542
<i>Within that reality,</i>

203
00:20:11,335 --> 00:20:15,547
<i>Sua was my pride and my hope in life.</i>

204
00:20:18,508 --> 00:20:20,677
Sua really wants to study abroad.

205
00:20:22,679 --> 00:20:23,722
Study abroad?

206
00:20:24,640 --> 00:20:28,227
She's a genius. A truly remarkable one.

207
00:20:28,310 --> 00:20:29,728
She's far too talented

208
00:20:29,811 --> 00:20:33,857
for the top high schools
and universities around here.

209
00:20:44,785 --> 00:20:46,870
She should go to a gifted school.

210
00:20:48,956 --> 00:20:53,168
If she does well,
she'll get a scholarship to study abroad.

211
00:20:55,796 --> 00:20:58,006
Here's a brochure
for overseas universities.

212
00:21:02,261 --> 00:21:05,430
It's not bad to rely on adults
once in a while.

213
00:21:11,520 --> 00:21:12,521
Johan.

214
00:21:13,355 --> 00:21:18,193
Through boxing,
you can make both your dreams come true.

215
00:21:18,277 --> 00:21:19,611
<i>This person…</i>

216
00:21:20,112 --> 00:21:22,906
<i>-</i>Let's give it a try.
<i>-Can I trust him?</i>

217
00:21:22,990 --> 00:21:27,577
<i>It was the first time</i>
<i>I felt this way about someone.</i>

218
00:21:31,748 --> 00:21:36,211
Already gassed? And you're the punk
who lost his college spot over a fight?

219
00:21:36,295 --> 00:21:37,629
You're gonna be champion.

220
00:21:37,713 --> 00:21:41,425
Your fists are sending your sister
to study abroad, aren't they?

221
00:21:54,021 --> 00:21:55,022
Last one!

222
00:21:59,693 --> 00:22:02,195
-Are you okay, Mr. Kang?
-Shut up.

223
00:22:05,157 --> 00:22:05,991
Let's go again.

224
00:22:06,074 --> 00:22:11,872
Put more power into it. Good. More!

225
00:22:11,955 --> 00:22:15,000
Finish it up!

226
00:22:15,625 --> 00:22:19,129
IS THE USUAL PLACE OKAY?

227
00:22:19,212 --> 00:22:20,213
OKAY.

228
00:22:20,297 --> 00:22:21,256
One more time!

229
00:22:22,716 --> 00:22:24,968
Wow, you're working hard.

230
00:22:29,806 --> 00:22:32,768
Johan, you're working on Christmas Day?

231
00:22:32,851 --> 00:22:35,687
Yeah, but I have
an important appointment before that.

232
00:22:35,771 --> 00:22:36,897
Bye then.

233
00:22:48,241 --> 00:22:51,244
What did you just say?

234
00:22:52,412 --> 00:22:56,583
Why don't you quit boxing?

235
00:22:57,417 --> 00:23:00,545
I think getting a stable job

236
00:23:00,629 --> 00:23:03,548
would be better for Sua's sake too.

237
00:23:07,928 --> 00:23:08,929
Well,

238
00:23:10,305 --> 00:23:16,812
you were the one who told me
to chase both our dreams.

239
00:23:23,276 --> 00:23:24,486
Yeah.

240
00:23:26,279 --> 00:23:27,489
That's true.

241
00:23:30,992 --> 00:23:32,994
That's exactly why I'm saying this.

242
00:23:35,580 --> 00:23:37,833
I was wrong.

243
00:23:37,916 --> 00:23:42,212
Dreams? Ideals? Do they even exist?

244
00:23:42,921 --> 00:23:47,175
After ten years of teaching,
I finally understand.

245
00:23:56,768 --> 00:23:58,228
Johan.

246
00:23:59,521 --> 00:24:05,735
Focus on what you can stick with,
rather than what you want to do.

247
00:24:08,864 --> 00:24:11,908
You can take it easy now.

248
00:24:13,160 --> 00:24:15,036
Let the weight off your shoulders.

249
00:24:16,413 --> 00:24:20,542
Living in reality isn't so hard.

250
00:24:22,169 --> 00:24:25,255
I'm going to quit teaching.

251
00:24:27,257 --> 00:24:30,010
I felt that I needed to tell you this.

252
00:24:31,636 --> 00:24:34,347
This will be the last time
I stick my nose in.

253
00:24:37,142 --> 00:24:39,561
<i>I had tried to live the best I could.</i>

254
00:24:41,438 --> 00:24:44,274
<i>I thought I had met an adult</i>
<i>that I could look up to.</i>

255
00:24:45,817 --> 00:24:47,819
<i>But even that person…</i>

256
00:24:49,946 --> 00:24:52,073
<i>was knocked down by reality.</i>

257
00:24:54,576 --> 00:24:58,205
<i>And he walked away from me.</i>

258
00:24:58,788 --> 00:25:00,916
AVAILABLE BALANCE
30,350 WON

259
00:25:00,999 --> 00:25:03,126
<i>Are some people</i>
<i>never meant to be rewarded…</i>

260
00:25:05,545 --> 00:25:07,547
<i>no matter what they do?</i>

261
00:25:13,595 --> 00:25:15,013
<i>Besides,</i>

262
00:25:15,514 --> 00:25:20,477
<i>what am I even struggling for?</i>

263
00:25:23,396 --> 00:25:28,026
<i>Why am I trying so hard</i>
<i>to live a good life?</i>

264
00:25:30,487 --> 00:25:31,863
Welcome.

265
00:25:42,290 --> 00:25:44,000
The next drink is on me.

266
00:25:47,629 --> 00:25:50,048
I'm Shim Gicheol, a boxing promoter.

267
00:25:50,549 --> 00:25:52,008
Uh…

268
00:25:53,343 --> 00:25:55,762
I might be able to help you.

269
00:25:59,558 --> 00:26:00,809
Please, have a seat.

270
00:26:00,892 --> 00:26:02,060
<i>The devil's whispers.</i>

271
00:26:02,143 --> 00:26:04,771
-Two of the same drink, please.
-Yes, sir.

272
00:26:05,689 --> 00:26:07,440
<i>Their timing is impeccable.</i>

273
00:26:07,941 --> 00:26:08,942
Take a seat.

274
00:26:12,028 --> 00:26:13,697
How are you still an amateur?

275
00:26:13,780 --> 00:26:15,532
<i>Because of this timing…</i>

276
00:26:17,993 --> 00:26:23,915
<i>the voice I'd normally ignore</i>
<i>reached my ears.</i>

277
00:26:25,625 --> 00:26:28,712
<i>From just three matches,</i>

278
00:26:29,629 --> 00:26:35,468
<i>I earned dozens of times more</i>
<i>than I did in my entire boxing career.</i>

279
00:26:36,886 --> 00:26:37,721
Do a good job.

280
00:26:39,055 --> 00:26:42,434
<i>-But I'm not sure why.</i>
<i>-</i>Yes, sir.

281
00:26:42,934 --> 00:26:46,229
<i>This was supposed to be</i>
<i>what I wanted, but…</i>

282
00:27:44,746 --> 00:27:45,955
I'm sorry.

283
00:27:47,499 --> 00:27:48,500
I…

284
00:27:50,001 --> 00:27:52,921
I was scared of being liked.

285
00:28:03,973 --> 00:28:04,974
Dammit.

286
00:28:11,272 --> 00:28:15,193
<i>I could tell right away</i>
<i>from looking at his eyes.</i>

287
00:28:17,153 --> 00:28:18,279
<i>We're the same.</i>

288
00:28:18,363 --> 00:28:22,242
-Why is it always me? Why?
-<i>He's just like me.</i>

289
00:28:34,087 --> 00:28:35,505
Hey, wait!

290
00:28:47,892 --> 00:28:51,020
<i>What I saw back then felt very strange.</i>

291
00:28:51,813 --> 00:28:56,943
<i>He looked like</i>
<i>he was trying to accept something.</i>

292
00:28:57,026 --> 00:29:00,071
<i>Something I could never</i>
<i>come to terms with.</i>

293
00:29:00,572 --> 00:29:01,406
Hey!

294
00:29:01,489 --> 00:29:06,870
<i>In that instant,</i>
<i>I knew I didn't want him to die.</i>

295
00:29:07,579 --> 00:29:09,622
<i>I don't know why I did it.</i>

296
00:29:10,915 --> 00:29:13,918
<i>My actions weren't logical.</i>

297
00:29:15,044 --> 00:29:16,921
<i>But thinking back on it now…</i>

298
00:29:17,005 --> 00:29:17,839
Hey.

299
00:29:17,922 --> 00:29:21,134
<i>…I think my heart</i>

300
00:29:22,051 --> 00:29:25,138
<i>had already been touched at that point.</i>

301
00:29:31,853 --> 00:29:33,229
<i>That's why…</i>

302
00:29:39,819 --> 00:29:42,238
Don't run, Hwang Johan!

303
00:29:42,739 --> 00:29:45,241
<i>…when I heard that voice in the ring,</i>

304
00:29:47,035 --> 00:29:49,662
<i>from a guy I thought I'd never see again,</i>

305
00:29:51,164 --> 00:29:55,376
<i>it honestly sounded like</i>
<i>the voice of salvation.</i>

306
00:29:56,711 --> 00:30:01,674
<i>In that voice, I found comfort.</i>

307
00:30:05,011 --> 00:30:06,679
Good work.

308
00:30:20,318 --> 00:30:22,028
RYU: GOOD LUCK.

309
00:30:22,111 --> 00:30:23,738
"Good luck"? Is he for real?

310
00:30:25,156 --> 00:30:30,453
I think he painted it while thinking
of someone special to him.

311
00:30:38,837 --> 00:30:40,713
You were trying to protect it, right?

312
00:30:40,797 --> 00:30:42,423
Your soul.

313
00:30:44,133 --> 00:30:46,553
It definitely felt like a miracle.

314
00:30:53,434 --> 00:30:54,727
This is delicious.

315
00:31:00,859 --> 00:31:04,904
<i>His feelings get hurt easily.</i>

316
00:31:06,114 --> 00:31:11,035
<i>And he thinks of himself as a weak person.</i>

317
00:31:12,495 --> 00:31:17,166
<i>But being able to feel hurt</i>

318
00:31:18,376 --> 00:31:20,044
<i>is an incredible thing.</i>

319
00:31:21,546 --> 00:31:27,093
<i>People who give up and drift through life…</i>

320
00:31:30,388 --> 00:31:32,265
<i>don't feel pain anymore.</i>

321
00:31:34,100 --> 00:31:36,644
<i>They're afraid of getting hurt…</i>

322
00:31:38,980 --> 00:31:41,357
<i>so they run away.</i>

323
00:31:41,441 --> 00:31:43,484
-You asked me to come to Japan.
-What?

324
00:31:43,568 --> 00:31:45,069
Don't look down on me.

325
00:31:45,153 --> 00:31:48,072
<i>But you still let yourself get hurt.</i>

326
00:31:49,324 --> 00:31:52,452
<i>And you haven't given up</i>

327
00:31:54,370 --> 00:31:58,166
<i>on getting involved with people.</i>

328
00:31:58,249 --> 00:32:00,376
-Ta-da. How is it?
<i>-You're strong.</i>

329
00:32:00,460 --> 00:32:04,964
-Whoa, that's good!
-<i>You're a really strong person.</i>

330
00:32:05,465 --> 00:32:07,175
-It looks like you.
-Does it?

331
00:32:08,134 --> 00:32:09,135
I…

332
00:32:13,014 --> 00:32:17,560
I changed because I was with Ryu.

333
00:32:19,437 --> 00:32:20,647
No.

334
00:32:23,107 --> 00:32:24,984
I was able to change myself.

335
00:32:28,363 --> 00:32:33,660
If I had told him about my illness…

336
00:32:40,625 --> 00:32:47,256
knowing Ryu, he probably would have
insisted on taking care of me.

337
00:32:50,051 --> 00:32:51,469
But you know…

338
00:32:55,139 --> 00:32:56,349
that…

339
00:32:59,185 --> 00:33:02,021
wasn't the happiness I wanted for him.

340
00:33:08,152 --> 00:33:09,028
But…

341
00:33:18,496 --> 00:33:20,498
I wanted you by my side when I died.

342
00:33:24,335 --> 00:33:27,797
I wanted you to be part of the last sight…

343
00:33:34,053 --> 00:33:36,264
I would ever see in this world.

344
00:33:52,363 --> 00:33:56,617
I'm glad you were able to meet Ryu.

345
00:34:29,650 --> 00:34:30,651
Hey.

346
00:34:34,447 --> 00:34:35,865
Why?

347
00:34:39,202 --> 00:34:41,412
Why are you here?

348
00:34:44,707 --> 00:34:49,754
If you're here…

349
00:34:51,839 --> 00:34:53,174
it makes me…

350
00:34:56,636 --> 00:34:59,388
want to live longer.

351
00:35:48,688 --> 00:35:50,314
We'll be off then.

352
00:35:54,986 --> 00:35:55,987
Bye.

353
00:36:14,672 --> 00:36:19,719
<i>You finally found</i>
<i>what you were looking for.</i>

354
00:36:23,347 --> 00:36:25,766
<i>You said softly…</i>

355
00:36:32,190 --> 00:36:33,900
<i>"This long journey…</i>

356
00:36:36,569 --> 00:36:38,070
<i>is almost over."</i>

357
00:36:54,587 --> 00:36:58,841
<i>I've met a lot of people until now.</i>

358
00:37:01,719 --> 00:37:05,014
<i>And of those people,</i>
<i>there are some I can't see anymore.</i>

359
00:37:09,894 --> 00:37:11,520
<i>You said to me…</i>

360
00:37:15,107 --> 00:37:17,652
<i>"You have a lonely look</i>
<i>on your face again."</i>

361
00:37:20,613 --> 00:37:26,077
<i>"Loneliness is an incredible invention."</i>

362
00:37:26,577 --> 00:37:27,578
We're here.

363
00:37:30,498 --> 00:37:32,375
<i>"Because feeling lonely means</i>

364
00:37:33,960 --> 00:37:36,337
<i>there's someone you truly care about."</i>

365
00:37:38,589 --> 00:37:40,800
<i>"Someone you really want to see."</i>

366
00:37:44,762 --> 00:37:46,514
How's Kanau?

367
00:37:49,308 --> 00:37:50,226
I'll show you.

368
00:37:53,020 --> 00:37:55,439
<i>"That's truly amazing."</i>

369
00:37:56,941 --> 00:37:57,858
A face mask.

370
00:37:57,942 --> 00:37:59,277
<i>"You know that, right?"</i>

371
00:38:08,369 --> 00:38:10,079
<i>I nodded.</i>

372
00:38:11,747 --> 00:38:13,749
<i>Tears welled up in my eyes.</i>

373
00:38:15,251 --> 00:38:17,253
She's starting to look like Seiichi.

374
00:38:17,336 --> 00:38:18,170
<i>Then…</i>

375
00:38:18,254 --> 00:38:19,213
And Sumiko's upset.

376
00:38:19,297 --> 00:38:24,885
<i>…the tears soaked up the light</i>
<i>and turned into beautiful crystals.</i>

377
00:38:33,144 --> 00:38:37,690
<i>I cry because</i>
<i>whenever I looked at something,</i>

378
00:38:39,317 --> 00:38:42,278
<i>you were always by my side,</i>
<i>watching it with me.</i>

379
00:38:47,616 --> 00:38:50,161
<i>And when you are looking at something,</i>

380
00:38:51,412 --> 00:38:56,083
<i>I would want to look at it too,</i>
<i>right by your side.</i>

381
00:39:01,505 --> 00:39:06,135
We've seen so much together.

382
00:39:14,185 --> 00:39:16,354
That came out of nowhere.

383
00:39:23,361 --> 00:39:25,029
It's a great story, isn't it?

384
00:39:31,994 --> 00:39:34,955
It's my story.

385
00:39:45,508 --> 00:39:49,720
So, wherever we are,
no matter what we're doing,

386
00:39:49,804 --> 00:39:51,764
we're never alone.

387
00:40:10,408 --> 00:40:13,619
<i>Where should we go next?</i>

388
00:40:15,704 --> 00:40:17,331
<i>Anywhere's fine.</i>

389
00:40:18,958 --> 00:40:20,376
<i>As long as I'm with you.</i>

390
00:40:24,130 --> 00:40:25,548
<i>Saranghae</i>.

391
00:40:27,883 --> 00:40:29,260
<i>I love you.</i>

392
00:42:48,065 --> 00:42:50,985
Subtitle translation by: Remi Miura
